[b]Class[/b]: Server
[b]Purpose[/b]: To show how to load this during boot.

[code]
static Security security;
public static void main(String[] args) {
        //boot logic here..

       security = new Security();//have to do this redudancy to get the filepath. or can just type in the string.
       Security securitytmp = (Security)SerialHandler.fetch(security.getFilePath());
if (securitytmp != null) //loaded the file correctly
security = securitytmp; //assigns the file.
    }[/code]
Upon the execution of this code:
Loads file devoted to Security.
If it loads, all of the Serializable data values will be restored to their previous state. If a value is not serializable, or should be excluded - mark it transient.
